{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b1dd0199-5784-4394-bbd6-1d209b41982d","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFix: swap the order so `Domain.fs` comes first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01YHxSs7Gnr8kBi6cDZeZFd5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-625e8223bf1f418888ff553236da4964/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-625e8223bf1f418888ff553236da4964/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"33df70be-3e1a-4dc5-bc80-e57742812f49","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":371,"requestId":"EC31:38E194:A7FA8B:D1B19B:6A012965"},"id":"94a32e88-c684-4461-acc7-50f30ec2491b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:57:16.707Z","parentId":"15d0dac7-571b-40be-b6d2-feaa113d6fad"}
